22 SECTION 2. LEGISLATIVE INTENT - COST REIMBURSEMENTS - LOAN
23 REPAYMENTS. It is the intent of the sixty-ninth legislative assembly that the attorney general
24 seek reimbursement from the federal government for the costs of responding to unlawful activity
25 associated with the construction of the Dakota access pipeline. It is further the intent of the
26 sixty-ninth legislative assembly that these reimbursements be used to repay the Bank of North
27 Dakota loans authorized by the emergency commission and the legislative assembly which
28 were obtained to provide the funding necessary to respond to the unlawful activity associated
29 with the construction of the Dakota access pipeline. It is further the intent of the sixty-ninth
30 legislative assembly that the provisions of section 54-16-13 apply to the loans, except that
31 emergency commission approval does not apply.
